description.narrative: Three emergencies marked 2021; the COVID-19 second wave from February to June, a relatively minimal plague epidemic (August to October) and the nutrition emergency in the Great South (the whole year). These were managed in a coordinated manner with some challenges but overall serving the most vulnerable families and minimizing children&39;s suffering, ensuring them access to a comprehensive package of health services, on top of other services such as malnutrition screening and management as much as access to water and sanitation. Funds allowing these responses were mobilized particularly for COVID and Nutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
